### 1. Get all tariffs (should be empty or show your test tariff)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tariffs

### 2. Create new tariff
POST http://localhost:8080/api/tariffs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test Premium WiFi",
  "downloadMbps": 100,
  "uploadMbps": 50,
  "durationHours": 24,
  "maxDevices": 5,
  "basePrice": 19.99,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "billingType": "ONE_TIME"
}

### 3. Get tariff by ID (use ID from step 2 response)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tariffs/1

### 4. Update tariff (use ID from step 2)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/tariffs/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Updated Premium WiFi",
  "downloadMbps": 150,
  "uploadMbps": 75,
  "durationHours": 48,
  "maxDevices": 8,
  "basePrice": 29.99,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "billingType": "ONE_TIME"
}

### 5. Get updated tariff to verify changes
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tariffs/1

### 6. Delete tariff
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/tariffs/1

### 7. Verify deletion (should return 404)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tariffs/1

### ERROR HANDLING TESTS

### Test 1: Invalid ID type (string instead of integer)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tariffs/abc

### Test 2: Negative ID
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tariffs/-1

### Test 3: Zero ID
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tariffs/0

### Test 4: Non-existent ID - resource not found
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tariffs/999

### Test 5: Missing required field in POST
POST http://localhost:8080/api/tariffs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "downloadMbps": 100,
  "uploadMbps": 50
}

### Test 6: Invalid data type in POST (string for number)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/tariffs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test WiFi",
  "downloadMbps": "not-a-number",
  "uploadMbps": 50,
  "durationHours": 24,
  "maxDevices": 5,
  "basePrice": 19.99,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "billingType": "ONE_TIME"
}

### Test 7: Validation constraint violation (negative price)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/tariffs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test WiFi",
  "downloadMbps": 100,
  "uploadMbps": 50,
  "durationHours": 24,
  "maxDevices": 5,
  "basePrice": -10.00,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "billingType": "ONE_TIME"
}

### Test 8: POST with ID provided (should be rejected)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/tariffs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": 5,
  "name": "Test WiFi with ID",
  "downloadMbps": 100,
  "uploadMbps": 50,
  "durationHours": 24,
  "maxDevices": 5,
  "basePrice": 19.99,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "billingType": "ONE_TIME"
}

### Test 9: POST with null ID (should work)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/tariffs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": null,
  "name": "Test WiFi with null ID",
  "downloadMbps": 100,
  "uploadMbps": 50,
  "durationHours": 24,
  "maxDevices": 5,
  "basePrice": 19.99,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "billingType": "ONE_TIME"
}

